summary: I've decided I wanted to try out doll repainting (if everything turns out well look forward to that), so I made this character...
caption:
I’ve decided I wanted to try out doll repainting (if everything turns out well look forward to that), so I made this character concept to start with.  (I also tried drawing her in a more semi-realistic style so I could translate that to doll form easier)
So her name is Moreiko (a combination of Mori and Yurei with -ko thrown in there as an ending to make it sound more like a name) and she is a japanese Yurei (ghost) who died in the woods and now helps lost travelers find their way out of the forest.

I did a lot of research on Japanese mythology and ghosts for this and I found out most ghost are dressed in all white kimonos with that little triangle thing on their head (I wasn’t sure what it was called so if anyone wants to let me know, go ahead).  So for her design I took a lot of inspiration from that and I added the red makeup around her eyes because that’s the kind of makeup geishas typically have and I like the way it looks on her.  As for the red in her outfit I put that there to kind of tie in with her makeup and so she wouldn’t be just completely white, so I just limited it to being a small accent color here and there.
